content: An enjoyable game book for any fan of wrestling, occasional cringey dialogue aside.
I know that you made this game a really long time ago, but please, make a part two. This game is very well made.

As a wrestling fan, sure I'm biased. I wished I could of started a faction "bullet club like". Kinda wish you allowed me to give me the gray tweener push like a randy orton. But it was great, it made me want more out of the game. From start to finish, this CYOA gave us the moral dilemma of choosing kayfabe and a straight shoot. I appreciate whoever made this one, a true wrestling fan would appreciate the quality of work and research you put into this. Please give me an expansion pack lol.

I didnt want this game to end. I cant help but think or maybe just hope that it could have gone on longer had I picked a different option. The ideas are interesting but at times hard to follow (match types mainly) and the blurring of kayfabe and reality got way out of hand near the end but it wasnt enough to ruin my experience. This game will definitely get a second playthrough at the very least.
A bit like modern day wrestling really. Really fantastic story lines, but not enough wrestling!

I love choice of games been playing for a while now from when there was only the first four games choice of romance, dragons, broadside, and vampires.. I thought the website would die out.. glad that it didn't
Love it
The writer did an amazing job, this was well worth the price.

As the overall rating hints this is one of the better stories on the play store. it does a good job of explaining wrestling terms and ideas. But as good as it is unless you have at least a passing interest in the medium you can probably pass. However, if you do or have ever so much as watched a wrestling match this is a GREAT read, no matter what the cheesy cover art may make you think.
I'm not even that big a fan of wrestling but I'll admit, this one of the best CYOA I've ever played, definitely worth the price.
very fun

I am not a big fan of wrestling. But something told me try this game, and I'm glad it did! The storyline immerses you in the wrestling culture, with amazing characters and fantastic writing in addition!
Haha I've played this so many times and only just realised they made a reference to stone colds 3:16 always find something new haha
Listen If they created a Slammed! 2, then I would most definitely play it. If they never made a Slammed! 2, then I would still replay this game because it is that damn good.

I'm not much of a wrestling fan so was a bit apprehensive of this game, but 
it was recommended to me by a friend. I absolutely loved it. I had to 
Google a couple of words but other than that I couldn't get enough. I 
played a face character which worked with my personality, but next time I'm 
going to be a bad ass heel (oh, and, Evelyn all the way) loved it loved it 
loved it.

The story is pretty nice, and the ndings are satisfying, I just wish that 
there was a sequel or something
worth every pennyveven if you are not a wrestling fan like me its amzing and brought real emotion

It's supremely well written and as a wrestling fan I love the references and the knowledge of the writer.  Also the characters are really well dine.  However the story is too limited and the choices more or less meaningless. It's a one track road where the most meaningful decision is "Punch Him", "Dropkick Him" or "Clothesline Him". And essentially no branching of the stories.  So as a story it is wondeful, some of the finest writing I've seen. As a Choose your own adventure style story, it's severely lacking.

Wow...I had never thought pro wrestling drama can be written into such touched tale ... not only the characters are lovable, they made you me feel like they really exist in this world... the Romance is totally touching and heart warming, Evelyn Ecstasy will be my favorite Romance partner in all interactive novels.. she is humble , caring and loyal to my character till the end, most importantly, she react in such a gratitude manner when my character maintain loyal to her without cheating, it make me feel like the choice to stay loyal to her is well worth it... This is such an under-rated interactive novel that deserves every Penny I paid
One of my favorite games of the last 10 years
As a wrestling fan I really enjoy the storytelling. The only thing that weirds me out is the Harley Quinn reference I'm a fan Comics too but I'm wondering why that's there.

As a life long wrestling fan, I've been waiting for a game like this. The characters are larger then life, the setting is amazing and I especially love how you guys did historical wrestling events, IE the higher power and Monday night wars. Just wish there was a sequel to see you win the world title and see your relationship with Evelyn and JJ deepen.

Great "game", really enjoyed it, it's a shame that people who like both wrestling and choose your own story novels are probably such a small demographic.  Excellent writing, great characters and dialogue, wish I had someone I could reccomend it to
Definitely worth the time and effort to read, you don't have to be a big wrestling fan to enjoy this beautifully written story.

Absolutely excellent. This story really focused on interpersonal relationships and it pays off. Like. It pays off a lot. MetaHuman was the first choice of game I played on mobile. This surpasses it.   It is also worth noting that I am not into wrestling. The setting is just that. It is a setting. It's what allows the interpersonal crises to at themselves out. I found myself getting super into it. I guess this story has that kayfabe it loves so much in spades.
Of games however only 4 stars as i noticed some spelling mistakes and you only get to properly wrestle a couple of times. Also you don't get to play as a real 'heal' which is a bit annoying.
So sad when it was over, but loved every minute of it!!

Might just be the best game you guys ever produced! The story wasn't rushed, was not predictable, and had a story. If I ever become a film maker I would call up this company and make a movie off of this game! Truly Legendary

I was skeptical of SLAMMED!, wrestling has never been my cup of tea. Yet this glitzy, richly written CoG breaks down the terms, the lingo, and wraps them up in a surprisingly engrossing plot. The character choices are numerous and highly satisfying, keep with the stats well and feel nicely impactful. The only downside is a twist in the plot which the game pigeonholes, but is forgivable as it turns the cogs for an excellent finale. A must buy for anyone after a punchy, glamourous few hours in the ring.
Suprisingly deep, suprisingly moving little wrestling game/story. For literate wrestle nerds everywhere.
This game brought me back me back to my old E-Fed role playing days. I loved it and would gladly pay for more wrestling themed stories!
This is by far my favorite one so far. I must have gone through this story at least 5 times already and I could easily go through again. Best $5 I've ever spent

An amazingly engaging and complete story, this is just about as good as it gets...I was only disappointed in the ending I got.. After all my character suffered through,I managed to rekindle the friendship between her and JJ but couldn't romance her.. I know romance isn't a huge focus point,(I made sure my character was crushing on her in college)but after all is said and done I felt like I was robbed of the choice to do so.. even after working so hard.. But I loved the last Montage you make before he match!
Definitely my favorite choice game so far
Grear so far seems very interesting but i had the awkward momebt of having the same wrestling name as another wrestler on the reality show lol

Trust the reviews, this is easily one of the best game books out there. It sucks you in and never lets go. Many twists and turns, and you can easily end the game early if you don't think things through.
Haven't been this satisfied in a long while.

Let me start of by saying I'm not a wrestling fan nor have I ever been one so the story at first was a little "meh" for me but as I continued to read I just got more and more into it I even got emotional to an extent! I'm not gonna spoil the story for anybody but I encourage any one who has been looking for a Choice of Game to seriously consider giving Slammed a try
Loved this from the first word to the last.  Definitely worth a few read throughs.  I cant stop reading more of their games/storys
This story pretty changed my perspective of it in a very positive way. I loved this.
words don't  do this  story  justice

Could say a lot about this one. It's much longer and more interesting than I expected, and as someone who has never understood why anyone would like pro wrestling, after playing this game I "get it". However, a little frustrated with choices that don't seem to matter and other choices that I can't make even after multiple different playthroughs.
Incredible storytelling. A real experience.

This was very well written, with good pacing, very good character development and choices that felt meaningful. I highly recommend this, even for people who are not great fans of wrestling. I've been playing game books for 30 years and this one is right in the top of the pile as fire as quality is concerned.

I'm no wrestler but love the sport and can imagine what goes on behind the curtain. Feels like its very probable that this story is very close to happening in real life somewhere to someone in the business of pro wrestling or trying to break into it. A long story is always appreciated as well as a quality experience

This is probably one of the top 3 best choice of games i ever played witch is all of them the story never gets boring and plenty of choices to keep you reading every word instead of just skimming through it definitely would buy the next game written by this author and if your new to choice of games this one would get you hooked
Its an excellent game but I wish you could create your own finisher and entrance.  Other than that,  its a good game
At first I was dubious as I'm not at a a fan of wrestling but it really is a great story.
Was put off by the wrestling theme, part of me still isn't much a fan, but this story gets better each read. Must own if you're into these Choice games.
I don't even like professional wrestling, but this story sucked me in. I played it twice through, and had a blast both times.

This game is a great read, however it feels more like a book at times because every choice isnt available to you everytime you read through. This causes the reader to be forced into choosing from very limited choices, opposed to choosing from the complete list of choices. Case in point breaking out of Tapuras submission hold.
Considering that I am not much of a fan of wrestling, I found it still interesting. It was engaging and you feel like you wouldn't mind replaying. Worth it
This is an absolute classic wrestling game.  The only thing it needed was a Terry Funk character to make it perfect!
Didnt think i would like it but it was awesome
Really well done, loved it from beginning to end. Hope to see more in the future!
This book is great because it takes you through the life of being a wrestler or a diva

SUPERR GREAT story line :D

Everything about this is great, the writing, the differing paths your wrestler can take, the epic story that unfolded, the knowledge of wrestling from the author, and even the small details from earlier choices made. I was dissapointed there wasn't more at the end, but that surely is only a good thing. Hoping for a sequel, or something at least wrestling related.
I knew almost nothing about wrestling before this game. The story's immersive, the characters diverse, and the actual fights are awesome!
This game is AMAZING. Better story than most real Wrestling shows my only gripe is you can't romance the boss but that's minor. A Must purchase

This story is full of twists and turns and drama and kept my heart racing at parts!
Great writing from beginning to end with your choices actually having an impact on the story.

The storytelling in this is absolutely top-notch. I played through twice in one sitting, no lie. And the impact of the choices I made were immediately noticeable but also shaped the scope of things as a whole. Can't wait to play through a third time and really shake things up haha. Very well done I highly recommend it.
Masterful representation of wrestling from the politics to the moves. The stats you build up really matter in this game, makes you very careful of your next choice.
Amazing. Hope there's a Slammed 2 soon
Solid CYOA game, the game does suffer from the occasional hand-holding but several of the story's key moments can vary dramatically based on choice. If your on the fence about it, get it.
Fantastic game.
The plot was awesome. The story length was great at keeping me stuck to it with its twists. Any wrestling fan will totally love this. Great work ppl..great work.*2 thumbs up*
I like this game.  The story is excellent,  the best interactif story so far. I recommend this game to anyone who like wrestling.
I was never really liked wrestling, but this games was actually really entertaining. The plot of the game is interesting and how it gives you different endings was fun.
Great game it gives you loads of choice and gives u a really gripping storyline as well.
I cannot tell you how deep I got into this, I got so fudging deep I cried, I laughed, and I felt, I don't even know about the wrestling world, but this got me hooked!
Best one I've played

Slammed! is a wonderful interactive story set in the world of professional wrestling. We all know that wrestling is scripted, and yet behind the storylines are real people with real issues; that's the perspective from which Slammed! is written, spinning a story of ambition, betrayal and redemption. If you're a wrestling fan, you'll find it quite true to life, not to mention packed with subtle references to famous performers. But you don't necessarily need any knowledge of wrestling to enjoy the story, as it tells you everything you need to know to appreciate wrestling's strange intersection of reality and fiction. (And just so you know: A lot of the story developments are inspired by real events--probably more than you would believe...)
Hope you can update it and continue the story love just disappointed it's over and doesn't keep going please update story or make another app that continues the story
Its an amazing story line with amazing characters. Couldnt stop even if I wanted to!

Really captures the imagination which is what I'm all about. I live the endless choices...

One of their best games in years, and a personal favorite of mine. This is particularly surprising, because I'm not a fan of wrestling at all. The characters are all great, and the situations the game puts you in are very fun. It's long, well written, and has a lot of humor and drama that flow well together. I highly recommend it, regardless of how you feel about wrestling, and I look forward to whatever the author decides to do next.
This is amazing. Really in depth and good writing. Easily worth the money. I'm on read through three currently and it's still amazing!

I dont even know that much about wrestling yet this is one of my favorite choice of games! I wasnt sure on buying yet so i waited for awhile & finally got it & I love it!! You will not regret buying this game!

One of the most well crafted stories in the choice of games roster. It's character development and story telling are definitely some of the best.

I really enjoyed it the first time I played, and was surprised to see how many different endings there are. Quite a bit of replay value, but having to go through the start bits so often and only see the effects at the end reduces my desire to replay... would be better with another fight to play in the early parts. Good fun though
Surprising

I was not sure about playing this at first due to wrestling.  Not a fan of it but this one was grand! I loved the story and a certain part happened that made me die as well when I read that part. I can't spoil it! Have to read it first but amazing and worth every cent and more.

I had some serious visceral and emotional reactions to certain events in the game and I, like many others, had a serious hate-on for at least one person through most of the game. XD It's a great CoG and I hope they make more like it in the future.

One of the best Choice of Games titles I've played, Slammed is a compelling story of real friendship and in ring rivalry -- and sometimes the other way around! Great choices and definite replayability.
I was a fish swimming around with nothing to do. And then this little hook appeared. I took a bite and I don't regret it at all. Well worth the price of admission.
Great story depth. 1 of my favourites
Deserves a sequel ala heroes rise.
Great read.

This is the first choice game I've played, and it's really really good. Im not known to be a reader. But this really sucked me in. Great story, characters and the romantic interests were well done. Longest review I've left for a game. I'd gladly buy more if others were of this quality.
I have no experience with any sort of wrestling and I have never been a fan of it, but I really enjoyed this Choice of game. I was able to get into the story with no initial wrestling interest.

The story is still very interesting even if you have little knowledge or interest in professional wrestling. The real gem here is the focus on the characters and the development of their role.    The only major issue I've had is that the story throws a large number of names and terminology, which I find pretty hard to keep track of. But thankfully perhaps, many of the names early on only have a small role. The important names tend to reoccur.   Overall, excellent "choose your own adventure" style game.
